<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="297" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d297">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 300.115/28352</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Commercial Adviser of the British,
                                    Embassy</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CSRF1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Crawford</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                    the Foreign Trade Adviser of the Department of State</hi>
                                    (<persName corresp="#p_RRF1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Rose</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-10">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 10, 1915</hi>.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr.</hi>
                                <persName corresp="#p_RRF1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Rose</hi></persName>: In reply to your
                                letter of the 6th instant, I concur that it is understood between us
                                that negotiations and arrangements which are being conducted by us
                                in the matter of facilitating the shipment of goods to and from
                                countries at war with Great Britain, and to and from neutral
                                countries contiguous to those countries, are to be regarded as
                                informal and unofficial and that neither of our Governments is in
                                any way committed thereby.</p>
                            <p>Yours very sincerely,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_CSRF1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">R. F. Crawford</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>